revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->

This template creates a header to be used with [[Template:S-start|succession boxes]] for people occupying [[Politician|political]] positions.

== Usage ==

The template was designed to default to {{s-start}}
{{s-off}}
{{s-end}} if no parameter is given. In the following table, the first column contains the header and the second column shows the template call used to create it.

{{s-start}}
{{s-off}}
| <code><nowiki>{{s-off}}</nowiki></code>
{{s-end}}

There are no parameters in this template.

== Example ==

From the [[Vladimir Putin]] article:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" style="font-size:95%; width:95%; overflow:auto;">
{{s-start}}
{{s-off}}
{{s-bef | before = [[Viktor Zubkov]]}}
{{s-ttl | title = [[Prime Minister of Russia]] | years = 2008–present}}
{{s-inc}}
{{s-end}}
</syntaxhighlight>
{{s-start}}
{{s-off}}
{{s-bef|before=[[Viktor Zubkov]]}}
{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Russia]]|years=2008–present}}
{{s-inc}}
{{s-end}}

== TemplateData ==
<templatedata>
{
	"params": {},
	"format": "block"
}
</templatedata>

== See also ==
* Documentation for creating succession boxes can be found at [[Template:S-start]].

